docs.abstract: Representative Scott Taylor, whose campaign has been rocked by a petition scandal, joins a handful of other Republicans facing accusations of misconduct and unexpectedly close races.
docs.snippet: Representative Scott Taylor, whose campaign has been rocked by a petition scandal, joins a handful of other Republicans facing accusations of misconduct and unexpectedly close races.
docs.lead_paragraph: VIRGINIA BEACH — Representative Scott Taylor, Republican of Virginia, has enjoyed a rapid political rise anchored in his valorous background as a member of the Navy SEALs, a credential with great resonance in a district that includes the world’s largest naval station and one of the highest concentrations of voters connected to the military. Fit, square-jawed and telegenic, he was expected to have a relatively easy time winning re-election in November.

headline.main: Scandal Shakes a Virginia House Republican, Adding to Electoral Tremors
headline.print_headline: Petition Scandal Imperils Virginia Congressman, Adding to G.O.P. Woes

docs.abstract: As the recreational vehicle industry deals with President Trump’s steel and aluminum tariffs, signs of a downturn in Elkhart, Ind., have people worried.
docs.snippet: As the recreational vehicle industry deals with President Trump’s steel and aluminum tariffs, signs of a downturn in Elkhart, Ind., have people worried.
docs.lead_paragraph: ELKHART, Ind. — The tables were filled at the Chubby Trout restaurant and the local craft beer flowed. The Flippin’ Cow was packed too, with diners overlooking Simonton Lake. Small manufacturing companies were advertising for workers, offering health insurance and retirement accounts.

headline.main: As Elkhart, Ind., Goes, So Goes the Nation, and Elkhart Is Nervous
headline.print_headline: Economic Bellwether Is Making a Midwestern City Nervous

docs.abstract: A meeting between President Trump and congressional leaders broke up without a deal, but he said talks will be held over the weekend.
docs.snippet: A meeting between President Trump and congressional leaders broke up without a deal, but he said talks will be held over the weekend.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump threatened on Friday to keep the federal government partly closed for “months or even years” if he did not get $5.6 billion for his wall at the southern border, and he warned that he was considering declaring a national emergency to build it without congressional approval.

headline.main: Trump Suggests Government Shutdown Could Last for ‘Months or Even Years’
headline.print_headline: Trump Prepared To Have Impasse Last for Months

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Michael Tackett

docs.abstract: The president’s comments and his encouragement of supporters in the crowd in Iraq and Germany veered from norms even as he upheld the convention of visiting soldiers abroad during the holidays.
docs.snippet: The president’s comments and his encouragement of supporters in the crowd in Iraq and Germany veered from norms even as he upheld the convention of visiting soldiers abroad during the holidays.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — During his surprise visit to American troops in Iraq and Germany this week, President Trump singled out red “Make America Great Again” caps in a sea of military fatigues, signed a “Trump 2020” patch and accused Representative Nancy Pelosi and other leading Democrats of being weak on border security.

headline.main: Trump Iraq Visit Is Called a Political Rally
headline.print_headline: President Crossed Political Line in Visit to Soldiers Abroad, Critics Say

docs.abstract: At the meeting, which was unusual for the spouse of a Supreme Court justice and a president, the activists denounced women serving in the military and questioned the administration’s hiring.
docs.snippet: At the meeting, which was unusual for the spouse of a Supreme Court justice and a president, the activists denounced women serving in the military and questioned the administration’s hiring.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump met last week with a delegation of hard-right activists led by Ginni Thomas, the wife of Justice Clarence Thomas, listening quietly as members of the group denounced transgender people and women serving in the military, according to three people with direct knowledge of the events.

headline.main: Trump Meets With Hard-Right Group Led by Ginni Thomas
headline.print_headline: Trump Is Said To Have Met Wife of Justice And Activists

byline.original: By Maggie Haberman and Annie Karni

docs.abstract: The former PepsiCo chief executive has been courted by Ivanka Trump, who is helping lead the search for a new World Bank president.
docs.snippet: The former PepsiCo chief executive has been courted by Ivanka Trump, who is helping lead the search for a new World Bank president.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House is considering Indra K. Nooyi, the former chief executive officer of PepsiCo, for the position of World Bank president, according to several people familiar with the process.

headline.main: White House Considering Indra Nooyi to Head World Bank
headline.print_headline: White House Considers Former PepsiCo Chief to Lead World Bank

docs.abstract: President Trump cited an array of statistics to paint a portrait of widespread criminal conduct by undocumented immigrants. Here’s the context behind them.

docs.lead_paragraph: Twenty-two days into the longest government shutdown ever, President Trump continued to press his case for a border wall. His tweet on Saturday was crammed with statistics that were either exaggerated or omitted important context.

headline.main: Explaining Trump’s Tweet on Crimes by Immigrants

docs.abstract: In Trump country, even some furloughed federal workers are backing the president’s wall demands, and keeping Republican senators in line as the shutdown stretches on.
docs.snippet: In Trump country, even some furloughed federal workers are backing the president’s wall demands, and keeping Republican senators in line as the shutdown stretches on.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARKERSBURG, W.Va. — On Day 20 of the partial government shutdown last week, a small band of federal workers, shivering in 25-degree weather, staged a rally to send what their organizer, Eric Engle, said was a message to Senator Shelley Moore Capito: “We need to end this shutdown. If it takes overriding the president, that’s what it takes.”

headline.main: Republicans Are in Lock Step With Trump on Shutdown. But for How Long?
headline.print_headline: Trump Country Calls On Party Not to Give In

docs.abstract: Three Democratic House committee chairmen cautioned that any effort to discourage or influence a witness’s testimony could be construed as a crime.
docs.snippet: Three Democratic House committee chairmen cautioned that any effort to discourage or influence a witness’s testimony could be construed as a crime.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Three newly empowered Democratic House committee chairmen, alarmed by statements over the weekend by President Trump about his former lawyer’s planned testimony before Congress, cautioned on Sunday that any effort to discourage or influence a witness’s testimony could be construed as a crime.

headline.main: Top Democrats Warn Trump Over Comments on Michael Cohen
headline.print_headline: Top House Democrats Issue Stern Warning to Trump Over His Comments on Cohen

byline.original: By Nicholas Fandos and Maggie Haberman
